title: Led Zeppelin - 1973.07.17 Seattle, Washington (Matrix)
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1973.07.17 Seattle, Washington (Matrix)   

Led Zeppelin
Seattle Center Coliseum
Seattle, Washington
July 17th 1973
Matrix (Audience and Soundboard sources blended into a single audio stream)

Audience Source: 
Incomplete excellent audience recording. The tape is great balanced and 
very clear audience recording. The sound seems to be recorded very close 
to the stage.

Soundboard Source: 
Incomplete excellent soundboard recording. The recording is a very good 
balanced professional board tape.

Tracklist:

CD 1 - MATRIX
1. Opening Announcements
2. Rock And Roll
3. Celebration Day
4. Black Dog
5. Over The Hills And Far Away
6. Misty Mountain Hop  
7. Since I've Been Loving You	
8. No Quarter
9. The Song Remains the Same
10. The Rain Song

CD 2 - MATRIX
1. Dazed And Confused
2. Stairway To Heaven

CD 3 - AUD source only
1. Moby Dick
2. Heartbreaker
3. Whole Lotta Love (medley)
4. The Ocean

Comments: 
Another of the great 1973 US Tour shows ... from the onset the band is ready 
to play and they take no prisoners! The show, surprisingly, was followed by 
a very long announcements: "Led Zeppelin has asked if we can get a few things 
straight tonight. Nobody around here digs any fireworks - please cool the 
fireworks. Please also, we have an area right here in front of the stage where 
we have many optic effects that we need to get off tonight, that we can't have 
any chance of anybody bumping the stage 'cos it'll completely ruin them. Their 
show usually runs about one hour and forty five minutes. If you can keep the 
fireworks down and keep everything off the front, Led Zeppelin would like to 
thank you and do about three hours tonight! So, sit back and stay cool and 
we'll have a long great show this evening!" The improvisations, especially 
No Quarter and the immensely long Dazed And Confused are fresh and unique and 
sound very different from anything heard before. The end has very unusual and 
exciting rhythm structure in Whole Lotta Love and Robert screaming as the band 
jam on the end of The Ocean
